        "simpler": "Resilience also grows from feeling capable, the sense that I can do hard things. That comes when kids get to try, struggle a bit, and recover while you stay close. If you fix everything for them, they miss the chance to feel capable. Often your job is to be nearby and steady, not to clear every hurdle.",
